<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The term "Hooverville" emerged during the Great Depression to describe:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Luxury housing developments promoted by President Hoover</option>
            <option letter="b">Shanty towns built by homeless and unemployed Americans</option>
            <option letter="c">Government-funded public housing projects</option>
            <option letter="d">Communities built for World War I veterans</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Hoovervilles were makeshift shanty towns named mockingly after President Herbert Hoover, whom many blamed for the Depression. These settlements, built by homeless and unemployed Americans, symbolized the economic hardships and the perceived inadequacy of Hoover's response to the crisis.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
